                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.112 Er 4/4.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister in temporary charge of the Embassy at
                            Constantinople</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-11-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 30, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Instructs to insist upon immediate reply to the representations made by the
                    embassy in regard to the deportation of Erickson from Elbassan and to report the
                    result to the Department by cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
